Gwynhyfar Foxfyre</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukalinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/29/01 1:54:02 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/Kalinn?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Broodmother</span><hr size=1> you CAN do the quest when she is out wandering.  when i did mine, i found her stuck in what looked like some pathing bug, she kept walking in a straight line until she hit the wall, would go up the wall, then warp back about 1/4 way across the zone and start again.  had to run and keep up with her, but handed in the harness, and she immediately turned and went back to her cave.  once she got to her cave, she left again and went to giant fort and finished off the quest. <p>-K<br>
